organize [OOSTT:00000042]
Value: 'organize' holds between an independent continuant and a planned process, iff the independent continuant particpates in the planned process and also participated in the creation of the plan specification that the planned process realizes.@en

Subject: authority [OOSTT:00000100]
Value: a socio-legal generically dependent continuant that is concretized in a role within an organizational context and which legally, normatively, or ethically permits some action.@en

Subject: statutory authority [OOSTT:00000101]
Value: authority prescribed by some enabling legislation@en

Subject: legislature [OOSTT:00000110]
Value: a governmental organization that has the authority to create, amend, fund, and repeal laws.@en

Value: an organization consisting of persons who bear committee member role where that organization is appointed by an organization or members of an organization to realize a role.@en

Subject: performance improvement committee [OOSTT:00000115]
Value: a committee whose function is to evaluate the system of care within a trauma center.@en

Subject: registrar role [OOSTT:00000116]
Value: a role that inheres in a homo sapiens that, if realized, is realized by preparing, keeping, and overseeing records made in a register.@en

Subject: committee member role [OOSTT:00000117]
Value: a role that, if realized, is realized in the organization context of a committee.@en

Subject: patient safety [OOSTT:00000118]
Value: a disposition realized in process profiles that have participants the biological qualities of patients and the practices and instruments of medical professionals.@en

Subject: has policy [OOSTT:00000123]
Value: 'has policy' holds between an organization and a directive information entity, iff the directive information entity is the outcome of a document act and it is meant to regulate the actions of the organization or its organizational members.@en

Subject: services geographical region [OOSTT:00000145]
Value: 'services area' holds iff a an organization performing or organizing paid or unpaid planned processes that benefit 3rd parties and b is a geographical region and a performs or organizes said planned process in the site of b.@en

Subject: policy of [OOSTT:00000278]
Value: 'policy of' holds between a directive information entity and an organization iff the directive information entity is the outcome of a document act and it is meant to regulate the actions of the organization or its organizational members.@en
